Try this.

(Assuming, type &amp; code are char &amp; time is int)

```java
String s = &quot;type: x, code: y, time: 25&quot;;
final String[] parts = s.split(&quot;,&quot;);
DTO dto = new DTO();
for (final String part : parts) {
     final String[] keyValue = part.trim().split(&quot;:&quot;);
     final String key = keyValue[0].trim();
     final String value = keyValue[1].trim();
     if (&quot;type&quot;.equals(key)) {
          dto.setType(value.charAt(0));
     } else if (&quot;code&quot;.equals(key)) {
          dto.setCode(value.charAt(0));
     } else if (&quot;time&quot;.equals(key)) {
          dto.setTime(Integer.parseInt(value));
     }
}
```

You can achieve that with **Jackson (`ObjectMapper`)**.

```java
// Raw data.
String data = &quot;type: x, code: y, time: 25&quot;;

// Mapper raw data to map.
Map&lt;String, String&gt; map = Arrays.asList(data.split(&quot;,&quot;))
        .stream()
        .map(s -&gt; s.split(&quot;:&quot;))
        .collect(Collectors
                .toMap(
                        s -&gt; s[0].trim(),
                        s -&gt; s[1].trim()));

// Jackson&#39;s ObjectMapper.
final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();
final MyDTO myDTO = objectMapper.convertValue(map, MyDTO.class);
```

1) Split entry pairs and convert string array to `List&lt;String&gt;` in order to use `java.lang.Collection.Stream` API from Java 1.8,
2) Map the resulting string list `key:value` to a string array with **`[0]`** as key and **`[1]`** as value,
3) Use `.collect(..)` terminal method from stream API to mutate,
4) Use the `Collectors.toMap()` static method which take two function to perform mutation from input type to key and value type,
5) All that&#39;s left is to convert the `Map` to `DTO` with the `ObjectMapper`.

**If there is a value in the raw data** that is not in the `DTO`, [see here to ignore it!](https://stackoverflow.com/a/7546047/2039546)

